{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 17:23:12.899856", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nSummary\n- Overall OSPF control plane across the backbone, distribution, and server-access routers is up and converged.\n- Server farm and 10.1.1.0/24 access segment exhibit normal end-to-end reachability.\n- A single user host (host_2_1_1_1) is experiencing end-to-end connectivity failure to all non-local 10.x destinations (including DNS and web servers).\n- Root cause: host_2_1_1_1 has an incorrect subnet mask (/8 instead of /24), causing on-link misclassification and ARP failures for remote 10.x destinations.\n\nKey Observations and Tests\n\n1) Host network configurations\n- host_1_1_1_1\n  - IP: 10.1.1.2/24, GW: 10.1.1.1\n  - Correct addressing for 10.1.1.0/24 segment.\n\n- host_2_1_1_1\n  - IP: 10.2.1.2/8, GW: 10.2.1.1\n  - Anomalous netmask: 255.0.0.0 (/8) instead of expected /24. Route table shows on-link 10.0.0.0/8.\n\n- dns_server\n  - IP: 10.200.0.2/24, GW: 10.200.0.1\n\n2) Control plane (OSPF)\n- Neighbors on all routers (core1/core2/core3/switch_dist_1_1/switch_dist_2_1/switch_server_access) are Full; adjacencies stable.\n- OSPF routes present and consistent:\n  - Core and distribution routers have routes for 10.1.1.0/24, 10.2.1.0/24, 10.2.2.0/24, and 10.200.0.0/24 with reasonable costs.\n  - switch_dist_1_1: 10.1.1.0/24 directly connected on br0; others via upstream.\n  - switch_dist_2_1: 10.2.1.0/24 directly connected on br0; others via upstream.\n  - switch_server_access: 10.200.0.0/24 directly connected; other 10.x via core.\n\nInterpretation: OSPF is healthy and advertises the expected prefixes; no evidence of control-plane failure.\n\n3) Data plane tests\n- From host_1_1_1_1 (10.1.1.2):\n  - Ping dns_server (10.200.0.2): success (0% loss).\n  - Ping web_server_0 (10.200.0.3): success (0% loss).\n  - Ping default gateway 10.1.1.1: success.\n  - Ping host_2_1_1_1 (10.2.1.2): timed out (no replies).\n\n- From host_2_1_1_1 (10.2.1.2/8):\n  - Ping default gateway 10.2.1.1: success (local L2/ARP OK).\n  - Ping dns_server (10.200.0.2): Destination Host Unreachable from 10.2.1.2 (indicative of ARP failure to an on-link IP).\n  - Ping web_server_0 (10.200.0.3): Destination Host Unreachable from 10.2.1.2.\n\n- From server network:\n  - web_server_0,1,2,3 -> dns_server: all succeed (0% loss).\n\nInterpretation: The 10.1.1.0/24 host reaches the server farm and DNS normally via routed path. The 10.2.1.0/24 host can reach its local gateway but fails to reach any remote 10.x destinations due to on-link misclassification, causing ARP failures instead of routing to the gateway.\n\nFault Localization\n- OSPF core and distribution devices: Healthy (neighbors Full; routes correct).\n- switch_dist_2_1 (gateway for 10.2.1.0/24): Correctly shows 10.2.1.0/24 as directly connected and routes to other networks present.\n- L2 connectivity on 10.2.1.0/24: Working (host_2_1_1_1 can ping 10.2.1.1).\n- DNS and web server segment: Healthy; reachable from 10.1.1.0/24 and internally.\n\nFault is localized to the endpoint host_2_1_1_1, not the network infrastructure.\n\nRoot Cause\n- host_2_1_1_1 is misconfigured with a 10.2.1.2/8 address instead of the intended 10.2.1.2/24. This causes the host to treat all 10.0.0.0/8 addresses (including 10.200.0.0/24 and 10.1.1.0/24) as local and attempt ARP on its local interface. Since those destinations are not on the same L2 segment, ARP fails, resulting in “Destination Host Unreachable” and no end-to-end connectivity beyond the local gateway.\n\nImpact Assessment\n- Users on the 10.2.1.0/24 segment, at least host_2_1_1_1, are unable to reach DNS (10.200.0.2) and server resources (10.200.0.0/24), and cannot communicate with other 10.x subnets.\n- Other segments (e.g., 10.1.1.0/24) do not show issues and can reach the server farm and DNS successfully.\n\nAdditional Notes\n- The network devices’ OSPF adjacencies and routing tables align with the expected topology.\n- No evidence of packet loss or instability across the core/backbone and server-access paths for healthy hosts.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 15568, "output_tokens": 3591, "total_tokens": 19159, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8448}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2304}}}
